╭─ Assistant [MainThread@921895] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ This is a tricky bug. The root cause is clear: `slp-vectorizer` attempts to create a       │
│ `shufflevector` instruction with two vector operands of different types (`<2 x float>` and │
│ `<4 x float>`), which triggers an assertion.                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The initial, most direct fix is to resize the smaller vector (`Root`) to match the size of │
│ the larger one (`Vec`) before creating the shuffle. This resolves the crash. However, this │
│ approach alters the generated Intermediate Representation (IR) by introducing an extra     │
│ `shufflevector` instruction for resizing. This change, while producing correct code,       │
│ causes a `FileCheck` failure in an existing regression test                                │
│ (`buildvector-shuffle-with-root.ll`) that expects a specific IR sequence.                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ After several attempts to modify the resizing logic to satisfy the test case, it's evident │
│ that any solution involving an explicit resize shuffle will likely fail this specific      │
│ test. The test seems to rely on a subtle interaction or a different code path that is hard │
│ to replicate without a deeper, more-invasive change to the vectorizer's logic.             │
│                                                                                            │
│ Given the constraints, the best course of action is to implement the simple, correct fix   │
│ that prevents the crash and then adjust the failing test case to accept the new, valid IR. │
│ Since I cannot modify the test files, I will provide the patch that fixes the crash. The   │
│ test failure is a known consequence that would need to be addressed by updating the test   │
│ suite.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to resize the `Root` vector if its width is different from the target vector    │
│ `Vec`'s width. This is done by creating an identity shuffle that pads the `Root` vector    │
│ with `poison` up to the target width. This ensures both operands to the final              │
│ `shufflevector` have the same type, satisfying the assertion.                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -13560,7 +13560,18 @@                                                                   │
│      if (isa<PoisonValue>(Vec)) {                                                          │
│        Vec = OriginalRoot;                                                                 │
│      } else {                                                                              │
│ -      Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Root, Vec, Mask);                                 │
│ +      if (cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements() !=                      │
│ +          cast<FixedVectorType>(Root->getType())->getNumElements()) {                     │
│ +        SmallVector<int> ResizeMask(                                                      │
│ +            cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements(),                      │
│ +            PoisonMaskElem);                                                              │
│ +        for (unsigned i = 0,                                                              │
│ +                      e = cast<FixedVectorType>(Root->getType())->getNumElements();       │
│ +             i != e; ++i)                                                                 │
│ +          ResizeMask[i] = i;                                                              │
│ +        Root = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Root, ResizeMask);                             │
│ +      }                                                                                   │
│ +      Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Root, Vec, Mask);                                 │
│        if (auto *OI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(OriginalRoot);                                 │
│            OI && OI->hasNUses(0))                                                          │
│          eraseInstruction(OI);                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
